						<p>On a slab built into the wall of the Tripurāntakēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1607, Raktākshi, Māgha śu. 7 = 1685 A.D., January 31.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the construction of probably a Śiva temple as a service to god Tripurāntaka by Āśaṁkana-Vīranna, son of Rāmarāju Gaṇaparāju.</p>						

